ps://schema.org/CreativeWork"><header class=3D"entry-header"><h1 class=3D"e=
ntry-title" itemprop=3D"headline">Goal Difference: What Does GD Mean in Foo=
tball and When Does it Matter?</h1>
</header><div class=3D"entry-content" itemprop=3D"text"><p>The only currenc=
y that truly matters in football are goals, and these have more of an impac=
t on the outcome of some tournaments than you might think.</p>
<p>When teams are level on points in the standings of some competitions, go=
al difference can be used to determine the ranking of said teams, and you w=
ill usually hear =E2=80=98GD=E2=80=99 spoken of a lot more as the football =
season winds down to its business end.</p>
<p>So what is goal difference, how is it calculated and which competitions =
still use it?</p>
<h2>What Is Goal Difference?</h2>
<p><img decoding=3D"async" class=3D"alignright size-full wp-image-1686" src=
=3D"https://www.rulesofsport.com/betting/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/goal-di=
fference-400px.jpg" alt=3D"Goal Difference" width=3D"400" height=3D"267">Qu=
ite simply, goal difference is the calculation of a team=E2=80=99s goals sc=
ored minus the number of goals they have conceded.</p>
<p>The best teams in the league will typically have a positive goal differe=
nce, simply because they net more goals than they conceded. By contrast, th=
ose in the lower reaches tend to have a negative number as their goal diffe=
rence =E2=80=93 by virtue of the fact they lose more games than they win.</=
p>
<p>All football leagues, and the group stages of tournaments like the Champ=
ions League and World Cup, are decided by the points tallies of the respect=
ive teams. But then two or more teams are level on points, goal difference =
is often used to separate them.</p>
<p>Many years ago, goal ratio was often used =E2=80=93 that was the number =
of goals scored divided by the number conceded. But that was thought to be =
unnecessarily complex, with the goal difference calculation much easier for=
 the =E2=80=98every man=E2=80=99 to work out without reaching for their cal=
culator.</p>
<h2>Which Competitions Use Goal Difference?</h2>
<p><img decoding=3D"async" class=3D"alignright size-full wp-image-1683" src=
=3D"https://www.rulesofsport.com/betting/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/premier=
-league-logo-400px.jpg" alt=3D"Premier League" width=3D"400" height=3D"241"=
>Some major football competitions have deviated away from goal difference a=
s their tie-break decider, using the head-to-head record of the teams invol=
ved as a differentiator instead.</p>
<p>The English Premier League still favours goal difference though, and whe=
n that=E2=80=99s level they go to =E2=80=98goals scored=E2=80=99 next.</p>
<p>In the Champions League, goal difference is only the sixth metric used t=
o separate teams in the group stage, with head-to-head results and head-to-=
head goal difference just two of the tie-breakers given preference.</p>
<p>The Spanish La Liga uses goal difference over head-to-head records, and =
bizarrely if those metrics are both level then the fair play record of the =
teams involved will be the next set of stats to be considered.</p>
<p>The German Bundesliga and French Ligue 1 also favour goal difference as =
their tie-breaker, although the Italian Serie A has pivoted away from GD to=
 head-to-head results.</p>
<p>Goal difference and then goals scored are the two main tie-breakers in t=
he World Cup too, with fair play record third on the list.</p>
<h2>Why Is Goal Difference Important?</h2>
<p><img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" class=3D"alignright size-full w=
p-image-1685" src=3D"https://www.rulesofsport.com/betting/wp-content/upload=
s/2022/11/football-manager-celebrating-400px.jpg" alt=3D"Football Manager C=
elebrating" width=3D"400" height=3D"267">As we=E2=80=99ve learned, goal dif=
ference can still play a major role in determining the outcome of some of t=
he world=E2=80=99s biggest football competitions.</p>
<p>It=E2=80=99s not uncommon for two teams to be level on points at the end=
 of the season, and so goal difference can be what separates glory from fai=
lure.</p>
<p>Punters that bet on outright markets, such as league winner, top four fi=
nish and relegation, also need to be aware that goal difference can ultimat=
ely determine the fate of their wagers.</p>
<p>It could be an agonising defeat=E2=80=A6 or a moment of ecstasy if your =
pick comes out on the right side of the GD calculation.</p>
<h2>What are GD, GF and GA In Football?</h2>
<p>When the league tables of pretty much any competition are published, a n=
umber of acronyms are used to make life easier for the reader.</p>
<p>Generally, you will see the team name on the extreme length and their po=
ints tally on the right, and in between a host of shortenings:</p>
<ul>
<li>W =E2=80=93 Games Won</li>
<li>D =E2=80=93 Games Drawn</li>
<li>L =E2=80=93 Games Lost</li>
<li>GF =E2=80=93 Goals For</li>
<li>GA =E2=80=93 Goals Against</li>
<li>GD =E2=80=93 Goal Difference</li>
</ul>
<h2>Has the Premier League Ever Been Decided On Goal Difference?</h2>
<p><img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" class=3D"aligncenter size-full =
wp-image-1684" src=3D"https://www.rulesofsport.com/betting/wp-content/uploa=
ds/2022/11/man-city-goal-difference-765px.jpg" alt=3D"Man City Goal DIffere=
nce" width=3D"765" height=3D"355"></p>
<p>The English top-flight has been decided on goal difference on two separa=
te occasions.</p>
<p>The first was in 1988/89, when the Division One title went down to the l=
ast game of the season in a titanic showdown between Liverpool and Arsenal.=
</p>
<p>With the score level on 1-1 at Anfield, the trophy was heading to the ho=
sts Liverpool. But then up stepped Michael Thomas with an injury-time goal =
for the Gunners, which stunned the home crowd and ensured Arsenal would win=
 the title on goal difference.</p>
<p>A similar scenario would play out in 2011/12, which will go down as one =
of the most dramatic campaigns in Premier League history.</p>
<p>Manchester City and their local rivals United were locked on points head=
ing into the final game of the season, but with City ahead by eight in the =
goal difference count, all they had to do was match the Red Devils=E2=80=99=
 result to win the title.</p>
<p>United won 1-0 at Sunderland and then heard with relish that City were l=
osing 1-2 at home against QPR.</p>
<p>Some were beginning to celebrate, but Edin Dzeko=E2=80=99s 92nd minute g=
oal halted that. And when Sergio Aguero scored that famous 94th minute winn=
er, City completed a famous comeback to ultimately win the Premier League o=
n goal difference.</p>
